    <item>
      <title>Understanding Continuous and Discrete Data</title>
      <link>https://vec6.com/en/blog/continuous-data-and-discrete-data/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 27 Oct 2020 07:35:35 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://vec6.com/en/blog/continuous-data-and-discrete-data/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In statistics, a type of data is collectively referred to as a variable. The data of a variable is called an observation, and the specific value of a variable is known as an observed value. For example, in the data below, &lt;code&gt;age&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;name&lt;/code&gt; are variables, while &lt;code&gt;18&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;&#39;Dahong&#39;&lt;/code&gt; are specific observed values.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-python&#34; data-lang=&#34;python&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;age, name&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;18&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;‘&lt;/span&gt;Dahong&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;’&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;21&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;‘&lt;/span&gt;Xiaohua&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;’&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Similarly, in statistics, discrete data is also referred to as discrete variables, and continuous data is called continuous variables. But how do we distinguish between the two?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
